definitions:
Financial intermediation indicators are indicators for estimating the size of a sector relative to the economy as a whole:                                                          1. The ratio of assets of the banking system to GDP; 
2. The ratio of the deposit base of the banking system to GDP; 
3. The ratio of the loan portfolio of the banking system to GDP

computation_methods:
The calculation uses published data on the official websites of the National Statistical Committee of the Kyrgyz Republic and the National Bank of the Kyrgyz Republic. The formula for obtaining indicators:                                                                                            Assets/GDP = Total assets of the banking system / annual GDP; 
Deposits/GDP = Total deposit base without banks / annual GDP;
Loans/GDP = Loan portfolio without financial institutions and banks / annual GDP, where Annual GDP is the sum of Gross Domestic Product values of the last 12 months. 
The data is used on an annual basis.
The data can be adjusted if the initial information changes
.
